                    </div>
                    <span>Don't know who Tommy Gun is or if he's actually from Chicago, as both authors of this book are and are well familiar with the area. Maybe he just doesn't realize that some street names and addresses have changed since 1929. Or mebbe he's related to R.J. Whatisname. Anyhow, seriously folks, this is a fantastic book and the most accurate examination ever of the most famous gangland massacre of all time. Helmer's notoriously lively writing style as usual makes for great reading. </span>
                  
